solve_summary {
  title "You solved {{puzzle_name}}!"

  timestamp {
    button "Timestamp this solve"
    waiting "Waiting for response from timestamp authority"
    success "This solve has been timestamped."
    error "Error timestamping solve: {{reason}}"
    (HoverStrings)hover {
      full "Timestamping"
      desc """
        Timestamping using a 3rd-party timestamp authority allows leaderboard
        verification for speedsolves of certain puzzles without video recording.
        Check the leaderboard rules for which puzzles are allowed.

        Fewest-move solutions never require video evidence or online verification.

        If you do not intend to submit to the leaderboards, you do not need to
        timestamp solves.
      """
    }
  }

  save {
    button "Save this solve"
    success "This solve has been saved."
    error "Error saving solve: {{reason}}"
    show_saved_solves "Show saved solves in file manager"
    show_this_saved_solve "Show in file manager"
  }

  table {
    this_solve "This solve"
    saved_pb "Saved PB"
    leaderboard_pb "Leaderboard PB"
    world_record "World record"

    move_count "Moves"
    time "Time"

    needs_sign_in "Sign into leaderboards to view"

    new_solve_is_faster "Your new solve is faster!"
    new_solve_is_shorter "Your new solve is shorter!"
    first_saved_solve "This would be your first saved solve in the category!"
    first_leaderboard_pb "This would be your first submitted solve in the category!"
    first_wr "This would be the first solve anyone has submitted in the category!"

    click_to_open_in_browser "Click to open in browser"
    click_to_show_in_file_manager "Click to show in file manager"
  }

  leaderboards {
    ineligible "This puzzle is not leaderboard-eligible"

    computer_assisted_fmc "This is a computer-assisted fewest-moves solve"
    will_upload_video "I want to add a video by editing the submission later"
    notes "Notes (optional)"

    needs_sign_in "You must sign into the leaderboards before submitting"

    submit "Submit to leaderboards"
    waiting "Submitting to leaderboards"
    success "Submitted to leaderboards"
    error "Error submitting solve: {{reason}}"
  }

  reopen_hint """
    You can reopen this popup by clicking on "Solved from a full scramble"
    at the bottom of the screen. It cannot be reopened after
    restarting the program or reloading the log file.
  """

  // appears when solving 3^4, 4^4, etc. but not 2^4
  solved_4d_1 """
    Congratulations on solving a 4-dimensional Rubik's Cube!
    You are now officially a Hypercuber.

    Before anything else: save your log file!
  """
  solved_4d_2 """
    You can also submit to the
    [Hypercubing Leaderboards](https://lb.hypercubing.xyz/)
    if you enjoy competition or want a
    public record of which puzzles you've solved.
    I encourage you to join
    our [Discord server](https://hypercubing.xyz/discord/)
    and [mailing list](https://groups.google.com/g/hypercubing)
    to connect with other hypercubers.

    You have learned so much by solving this puzzle. I'm proud of you.
  """
  solved_4d_history_title "A Brief History"
  solved_4d_history """
    To the best of our knowledge, [Andrey Astrelin](https://superliminal.com/andrey/)
    became the first person to simulate and solve a 4-dimensional Rubik's cube
    sometime around 1987, although the rest of the Hypercubing community would
    remain unaware until 2010.

    In 1988, Don Hatch and Melinda Green built the first version of
    [Magic Cube 4D](https://superliminal.com/cube/) and Don Hatch solved it.
    They also started a mailing list, which saw a slow trickle of
    solutions starting in 2000. More than 400 people solved the
    puzzle over the next 20 years, including myself in 2016.

    In 2021, Rowan Fortier started a Discord server to supplement the mailing list.
    Talking with folks there inspired me to extend an old keyboard-controlled
    Rubik's cube simulator of mine to support 4 dimensions.
    This program would eventually become Hyperspeedcube.
    You can read more about its development on the
    [Hypercubing Wiki](https://hypercubing.xyz/software/hyperspeedcube/),
    which also includes some screenshots of early prototypes.
  """
  // appears when solving any nontrivial n^5
  solved_5d """
    Congratulations on solving a 5-dimensional Rubik's Cube!

    > You have achieved ultimate super-nerd status.
    >
    > Take a few moments and space out on the ridiculousness
    of what you have just accomplished, then send your log file
    to roice@gravitation3d.com to get your name listed in the
    [MagicCube5D Hall of Insanity](http://www.gravitation3d.com/magiccube5d/hallofinsanity.html).

    ~ Roice Nelson
  """
  // appears when solving any nontrivial n^6
  solved_6d """
    Congratulations on solving a 6-dimensional Rubik's Cube!

    This is truly absurd.

    Send your log file to
    MagicCube4D@superliminal.com to get your name listed in the
    [MagicCube7D Hall of Fame](https://superliminal.com/andrey/mc7d/).

    And of course, if you haven't already, I encourage you to join
    our [Discord server](https://hypercubing.xyz/discord/)
    and [mailing list](https://groups.google.com/g/hypercubing).
  """
  // appears when solving any nontrivial n^7
  solved_7d """
    Congratulations on solving a 7-dimensional Rubik's Cube!

    > Imaginary mountains build themselves from our efforts to climb them,
    and it's our repeated attempts to reach the summit
    that turns those mountains into something real.

    ~ Bennett Foddy

    Send your log file to
    MagicCube4D@superliminal.com to get your name listed in the
    [MagicCube7D Hall of Fame](https://superliminal.com/andrey/mc7d/).

    And of course, if you haven't already, I encourage you to join
    our [Discord server](https://hypercubing.xyz/discord/)
    and [mailing list](https://groups.google.com/g/hypercubing).
  """
  // appears when solving any nontrivial n^8
  solved_8d """
    Congratulations on solving an 8-dimensional Rubik's Cube!

    At the time of writing, no one has ever solved this puzzle.
    You are probably the first person ever to read this message,
    and I honestly never thought anyone would do this.

    Take your world record. You've earned it.
  """

  support_request """
    I've dedicated thousands of hours over 5+ years to developing
    Hyperspeedcube and published it free of charge under a permissive license
    because I want everyone to have access to it. If you'd like to help me
    in my quest to make Hyperspeedcube
    the most powerful twisty puzzle simulator on the planet,
    consider [supporting me on Ko-fi](https://ko-fi.com/ajfarkas/).

    Thank you so much for using my software. It means the world to me. ♥
  """
}

help {
  log_vs_replay """
    **Log files** contain the initial scramble and the moves done to solve the puzzle.
    A **log file** is sufficient to prove that you have solved the puzzle in a certain number of moves.

    **Replay files** contain additional information about exactly how you executed moves, what moves were undone and redone, and when.
    **Replay files** may be required for speedsolving verification.
  """
  cant_save_replay "⚠ This solve was not loaded from a replay file so it cannot be saved as one."
  filter_styles """
    # Filter styles

    Filter styles can be applied to pieces using the **piece filters** tool.
  """
  color_assignments """
    # Color assignments

    Each facet on the puzzle is assigned a different color.
    {{dragging?
    Drag a facet name to assign a different color to it.
    }}
    In addition to the color scheme settings, you can **{{color_reassign_mousebind}}** a sticker to change its color assignment.

    - Single colors are best for small puzzles
    - Color sets are best for medium puzzles
    - Gradients are best for large puzzles
    - Colors within a color set are designed to contrast with each other and with other color sets of the same size

    Color values can be customized in the **global color palette** settings.
  """
  global_color_palette """
    # Global color palette

    The global color palette provides a way to change colors across all puzzles at once.

    For example, you can select a particular shade of red to use on every puzzle with red stickers.

    ## Color sets

    Some colors are organized into sets of colors that are similar but still contrast with each other.

    For example, a puzzle with two different shades of red needs those shades to be distinguishable, so it uses the "red dyad" from the global color palette.

    ## Color schemes

    The color scheme for any particular puzzle can be customized in the **color scheme** settings.
  """
  piece_filters """
    # Piece filters

    TODO: explain filters

    - Piece filters are per-puzzle
    - Filters auto-save when editing. click a preset to edit it
    - Creating a preset uses current rules
    - Ad-hoc = don't auto-save to a preset
  """
  piece_filter_presets """
    # Piece filter presets

    TODO: explain filter presets
  """
  piece_filter_sequences """
    # Piece filter sequences

    TODO: explain filter sequences
  """
  presets """
    # Presets

    A **preset** is a saved set of values that can be loaded at any time.

    - **Click** the `+` button to create a preset
    - **Click** a preset to activate it
    - **Right-click** a preset to rename or delete it
    - **Drag** a preset to reorder it

    Loading a preset discards unsaved changes.
  """
}

